COMMAND A PREMIUM showed early speed, prompted the moderate early pace while three wide on the first turn, kept close attendance to the pacesetter to the quarter marker, dropped back nearing mid-stretch and tired. MR BOTANICALS forwardly placed into the first turn, saved ground into the backstretch run, within range to the quarter marker, outrun to the furlong pole and gave way in the final furlong.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: COUNCILWOMAN JILLY showed early speed and prompted the pace into the first turn, kept close attendance to BOSSY PEGASUS through modest fractions to the half-mile marker, confronted that rival nearing the quarter marker, battled under firm urging to mid-stretch, shook free from a game BOSSY PEGASUS in deep stretch and just lasted over the oncoming runner-up. KITTEN CALLS unhurried in the early going, raced two wide into the backstretch run, came three wide into the second turn, rallied six wide for the drive, closed with a rush inside of the furlong pole, came within aim of COUNCILWOMAN JILLY in deep stretch and just missed for the win, while holding safely for second. BOSSY PEGASUS broke alertly and was sent to the early lead, set modest fractions while prompted to the quarter marker, was confronted by COUNCILWOMAN JILLY in upper stretch, battled with that foe to mid-stretch, could not keep pace in the final stages, was gamely bested and held well in the end for third. ON VACATION allowed to settle, saved ground to the second turn, rallied in upper stretch, could not sustain that bid in the final furlong and flattened out. CAL ROUGH bumped at the start and away a step slowly, was a bit keen while tracking the pace on the first turn, maintained position to the half-mile marker, lost ground two wide on the second turn, swung four wide for the drive and gave way. BEA MISCHIEF bumped CAL ROUGH and bothered PEACEHAVEN at the break, forwardly placed in the early stages, three wide along the first turn, stalked the modest pace to the far turn, dropped back in upper stretch and weakened.

RACE.FOOTNOTES: FIRST PREMIO settled in the second flight, was well placed through the backstretch run, ran two wide to the quarter marker, angled four wide approaching the top of the lane, assumed command inside of the furlong marker, attempted to hang in deep stretch and kept to task in the final strides to prevail. NOLDE was a bit fractious in the gate, broke out at the start and was off a step slowly, settled in the second flight through the backstretch run, advanced three wide nearing the quarter marker, came within aim in mid-stretch, could not match strides with FIRST PREMIO nearing the sixteenth-marker, came again when the winner attempted to hang in the final strides and was gamely bested for the win, while besting the rest. BRONZE WARRIOR raced three wide into the first turn, tracked the loose pacesetter to the second turn, advanced two wide in upper stretch, came in tight between runners nearing the furlong pole, could not keep pace in the final sixteenth and was just edged for show in the final strides. RACE.RACE_TEXT: GOLDEN GATE FIELDS RACE 9 5 1/2F All Weather Track CR: 75. Maiden Claiming Purse 17000. FOR MAIDENS, FILLIES THREE YEARS OLD. Weight, 120 lbs. Claiming Price $25,000, if for $22,500, allowed 2 lbs.
RACE.FOOTNOTES: A ROUSING BABE forwardly placed early, moved up to challenge BRONZE LADY for the lead passing the three furlong marker, engaged that one with a quarter mile to go, battled from there to the wire gaining the upper hand in the last strides. BRONZE LADY broke sharply and went straight to the front, established a clear lead to the turn, held the lead to the top of the stretch, met the challenge of A ROUSING BABE from the quarter, dueled gamely to the end but was outfinished in the shadow of the wire. GET MY POINT away well, was allowed to settle into a stalking position while saving ground through early going, shifted out to the four path for clear running at the top of the stretch and finished well but came up a bit short. RAUCOUS TIZZY raced in the back half of the field through the early stages, stayed in the clear through the turn, begin a sustained bid with three furlongs to go, swung out six wide at the top of the late, took the path of LUCKY LOCKETT near the 1/4 pole, was gaining but had too much ground to make up. STANDFORGRIT broke well and angled over from the outside, settled off the flank of BRONZE LADY down the back stretch, switched to the inside approaching the turn, responded to heavy pressure three furlongs out and remained a threat mid-stretch and weakened late. MO TOWN GAL was up with the chasing pack through the first quarter mile, began a strong bid through the turn and loomed boldly at the top of the stretch but flattened out with a furlong to go. SHE'S FANCY LIKE got a good position early, saved ground through the turn, came under pressure from the five-sixteenths and finished with some interest while never a serious threat. HOT LINK unable to keep up in the early stages, moved to the rail to save ground, was ridden from the half-mile pole but lacked a response. HALLELUJAH BABY devoid of early speed, fell well behind and chased the field to the stretch, kept on and managed to pass one in the late stages. LUCKY LOCKETT off slowly, settled into stride at the back of field for the first quarter, made a mild middle race move, steadied near the eighth pole off the heels of RAUCOUS TIZZY and was not persevered with from there.
